<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n37009k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n37" href="#n37009k">N37 (VI.B.28A)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n37all.htm#n37009k"> 9(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 209 The Greatest Man</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[<font size="-1">SUNDRIES AND AN AUTOBIOGRAPHY</font>]</font>: Barnum was now forty years old. &hellip; The first decade of Barnum&apos;s extraordinary career was summed up in the following verses published in 1851 in the <cite>Albany Argus</cite>: <mark>THE GREATEST MAN</mark> / What man, of all the nation&apos;s host, / Now fills the public eye the most, / By ever being at his Post? / Why, Barnum! &hellip; <font color="green">[And so on in like vein the verse proceeds.]</font> <small> M.R. Werner, <a name="MRWP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MRWP"><cite title="source">P.T. Barnum</cite></a> (1923) 209</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
